<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-01-23T16:40:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-01-23T16:40:00-05:00" n="775" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d775">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">839.00/2302: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Dominican Republic</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Russell</hi></persName>)
                                <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santo
                                        Domingo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-01-23T17:00:00-04:40"><hi rend="italic">January 23,
                                        1921—5 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received January 24—2:05
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>4. The four members of former Advisory Council and President of the
                            Supreme Court have signified their willingness to accept membership on
                            the Commission. …</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Russell</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>